article.headline: South Florida 74, Wright St 59
article.story: TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- Jimmy Baxter scored 22 points and fellow senior Gerrick Morris had 11 rebounds, 10 blocked shots and eight points to lead South Florida past Wright State 74-59 on Saturday. Brian Swift added 13 points and Bradley Mosley had 11 as the Bulls improved to 3-0 under first-year coach Robert McCullum. Senior guard Vernard Hollins scored 22 points and freshman forward Vova Severovas added 12 for Wright State (0-2). Hollins had four of only six assists for the Raiders. Morris blocked seven shots as South Florida built a 30-22 halftime lead. Three years ago, the 6-foot-10 center set a Conference USA record with 11 blocked shots as a freshman. Despite making only nine of 34 shots in the first half, Wright State trailed by just three points with two minutes left in the half. South Florida then went on a 10-2 run that lasted early into the second half. A pair of free throws by Marlyn Bryant gave the Bulls their largest lead at 74-57 with a minute to go in the game. The Raiders were no closer than seven points down after Severovas scored the first basket after the intermission.
